      • setParent

        protected void setParent(PARENT parent)
        This method sets the parent of this GenericTreeNode.
        Parameters:
        parent - is the parent to set. It may be null. However you should typically only call this method once with a non-null argument. It is still legal to re-arrange the tree-structure on existing GenericTreeNodes.

      • getChildren

        public List<CHILD> getChildren()
        This method gets the List containing all children of this GenericTreeNode. The List may be empty - in such case we call this GenericTreeNode a leaf . Each item of the returned List is called a child or child-node. It should return this GenericTreeNode as parent.
        Specified by:
        getChildren in interface GenericTreeNode<CHILD extends Node<PARENT>,PARENT extends GenericTreeNode<CHILD,PARENT>>
